      <para id="id1170853864248">Three different forms of each word (<emphasis effect="bold">small</emphasis> and <emphasis effect="bold">happy</emphasis>) have been used.</para>
      <para id="id1170853673628">How do I know when to use which form of the word.</para>
      <para id="id1170854945922"><emphasis effect="bold">CLUE</emphasis>: When comparing 2, add __ to the end of the word.</para>
      <para id="id1170853774913">  When comparing 3 or more, add __ to the end of the word.</para>
      <para id="id1170853835909">This will help!</para>
      <list id="id1170852373320" list-type="bulleted">
        <item>double the final consonant if it follows a short vowel, e.g. fat fa<emphasis effect="bold">tt</emphasis>er fa<emphasis effect="bold">tt</emphasis>est</item>
        <item>In words ending in <emphasis effect="bold">y </emphasis>, the y changes to <emphasis effect="bold">i</emphasis> before adding <emphasis effect="bold">–er</emphasis> or <emphasis effect="bold">–est</emphasis> e.g. happy happ<emphasis effect="bold">ier</emphasis>; happ<emphasis effect="bold">iest</emphasis>.</item>
        <item>If the word ends in <emphasis effect="bold">e</emphasis>, only add <emphasis effect="bold">–r</emphasis> or <emphasis effect="bold">–st</emphasis>, e.g. pale paler palest</item>
        <item/>
        <item>Try these:</item>
