      <para id="id1170853824605"/>
      <para id="id1170853556077">Rewrite the following, using the proper form of the adjective in brackets.</para>
      <list id="id1170853444785" list-type="bulleted">
        <item>Bill Gates is the (rich) man in the world.</item>
        <item>Andrea is (young) than Pete.</item>
        <item>It was the (worse) toothache I have ever had.</item>
        <item>It is the (less) I can do to help.</item>
        <item>
          <list id="id1170853555481" list-type="bulleted">
            <item>My toads hops the (fast) of all the toads.</item>
          </list>
        </item>
        <item/>
      </list>
      <para id="id1170853538859">Adjectives with three or four syllables don’t sound right when -er or -est are added. So, we use <emphasis effect="bold">more</emphasis> or <emphasis effect="bold">most</emphasis>.</para>
      <para id="id1170853506962">It is <emphasis effect="bold">more dangerous</emphasis> to climb a mountain without a safety harness.</para>
      <list id="id1170852623748" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic">
        <item>That bicycle is __ <emphasis effect="bold">expensive</emphasis> than this one.</item>
        <item>This is the __ <emphasis effect="bold">comfortable</emphasis> chair in which I have ever sat.</item>
        <item>You must be __ <emphasis effect="bold">careful</emphasis> with your books, Anne!</item>
        <item>This is the __ <emphasis effect="bold">exciting</emphasis> story I have ever heard.</item>
        <item>He is the __ <emphasis effect="bold">impatient</emphasis> person I know.</item>
      </list>
      <para id="id1170852721653">
        <emphasis effect="bold">Can you think of any others like this?</emphasis>
      </para>
      <para id="id1170853498201">
        <emphasis effect="bold">[LO 4.4.2]</emphasis>
      </para>
      <para id="id1170856037774">JUST FOR FUN.</para>
      <para id="id1170854951608">“PICTURE-A-NOUN!”</para>
      <list id="id1170855015836" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic">
        <item>Think of a noun.</item>
        <item>List 15 – 20 words describing this object.</item>
