      </list>
      <para id="id1170853746740"/>
      <para id="id1170853847278">(earthworm)</para>
      <para id="id1170853504316">ADVERBS</para>
      <para id="id1170853536753">Let’s recap</para>
      <para id="id1170854631198">An adjective describes the __  and an adverb describes the <emphasis effect="bold">ACTION</emphasis>!</para>
      <para id="id1170853774261">
        <emphasis effect="bold">Let’s play a game! This is how it works:</emphasis>
      </para>
      <list id="id1170852401761" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic">
        <item>Decide on an adverb, e.g. <emphasis effect="italics">quickly</emphasis>.</item>
        <item>Don’t tell anybody what you have chosen.</item>
        <item>A volunteer goes to the front of the classroom and the class gives him or her an action to do, e.g. brushing his teeth.</item>
        <item>He then has to act out the action of, e.g. brushing these teeth, in the manner of the adverb he has chosen.</item>
        <item>The class must guess what his adverb is.</item>
        <item>Each person has a turn to act.</item>
      </list>
      <para id="id1170855012728">
        <emphasis effect="bold">Choose an adverb from the puffy cloud. Use it in a sentence.</emphasis>
      </para>
      <para id="id1170854940834">
        <emphasis effect="bold">Select the most suitable adverb from between brackets.</emphasis>
      </para>
      <para id="id1170853845628">1. He cuddled the tiny puppy (roughly; tenderly; quickly).</para>
      <list id="id1170854881158" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic">
        <item>A hug bear attacked the tourist (savagely; carefully; weakly).</item>
        <item>My strong friend lifted the crate (easily; weakly; unhappily).</item>
        <item>The whale chased the fish (lazily; slowly; hungrily) round the bay.</item>
        <item>The exhausted crew sailed their yacht (energetically; carelessly; slowly) into the harbour.</item>
      </list>
      <para id="id1170853533838">Adverbs tell us HOW, WHEN and WHERE</para>
      <para id="id1170853673444">Now fill in the missing adverbs, rewriting the sentence in full and using the word in brackets as a clue.</para>
      <list id="id1170853562571" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic">
        <item>He ran to the shop __ (when)</item>
        <item>He ran to the shop __ (how)</item>
        <item>(When) __ I paid all the accounts.</item>
        <item>(How) __ he got off his chair and stomped out of the room.</item>
        <item>She ran __ (where)</item>
        <item>I have searched __ (where)</item>
      </list>
      <para id="id1170853829491">Complete these sentences by filling in the missing adverbs:</para>
      <list id="id1170852624035" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic">
        <item>Mr Riddle grew (how) __ excited when he saw his formula </item>
      </list>
      <para id="id1170853720096">working.</para>
      <list id="id1170853612486" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic">
        <item>He (how) __ pressed a large button and a (how) __ rumbling came from the test tube.</item>
        <item>(when) __ the whole contraption began to shake (how) __ and gas began to hiss (where) __ out of various tubes.</item>
        <item>Mr Hugland noticed (when) __ those bubbles were creeping </item>
      </list>
      <para id="id1170853776953">(how) __ up the insides of the little glass tubes and squirting </para>
      <para id="id1170853851755">(how) __  into the great jar (where) __ .</para>
